output:
# Maurice Strong and UNEP

Maurice Strong was elected as the first Executive Director of the United Nations Environment Programme (UNEP) by the UN General Assembly in **December 1972**.

This followed the historic UN Conference on the Human Environment held in Stockholm in June 1972, which led to the establishment of UNEP as a coordinating body for environmental activities within the UN system.
